    <h1>Aunetic's cookie policy</h1>
    <p>Aunetic Holding AB uses cookies at our webpage <a href="http://www.aunetic.com">www.aunetic.com</a> to optimize your experience.</p>
    <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
    <p>A cookie is a small text file containing information that is stored on your computer when you visit a website (or on a similar device with internet access, such as a tablet or mobile phone). Cookies are used to make websites function more efficiently, but also to provide certain information to the owner of a website. For example, this can involve saving language preferences or other settings to make it easier for the visitor during their next visit. Cookies make it possible to distinguish between different users, which in turn can provide each user with a more positive experience of the website.</p>
    <h2>Types of cookies</h2>
    <p>There are two types of cookies: permanent cookies and session cookies. At Aunetic’s website we use both types of cookies. Permanent cookies are stored as a file at the computer for a certain time until you or the server that sent them delete the cookies. Session cookies are stored temporarily when you visit the webpage and disappears when you close the browser.</p>
    <p>We use cookies to facilitate the use of our website, but also to adapt the experience for the individual user. However, the information collected does not contain any personal data but is used to determine certain visitor patterns regarding the use of our website. In addition, we do not save any IP-addresses to define specific visitor’s patterns at the webpage. Because of that, the information collected can never be connected to your identity.</p>
    <p>Moreover, Aunetic.com uses cookies to calculate and report website traffic and the number of users. We also use so-called third-party cookies from other companies for surveys and to measure website traffic.</p>
    <p>At Aunetic’s website, content from social media (such as LinkedIn, Facebook, and Instagram) may be embedded in the website. These suppliers may use cookies at Aunetic’s webpage. Aunetic does not have access to and cannot control neither these cookies or the personal data and information collected. Hence, you need to visit these suppliers’ websites to receive further information on their use of cookies, the information collected, and how you can block these.</p>
    <h2>Erasure and blocking of cookies</h2>
    <p>In the settings of your browser, you can block and delete cookies. The practical details of blocking and deletion differs between various browsers, but specific information on how your browser works can be found in the instructions of the browser or in the help section that is available in most browsers. Additional information concerning cookies can be accessed at <a href="http://www.aboutcookies.org">www.aboutcookies.org</a>.</p>
    <h1>Aunetic Cookies</h1>
    <p>These are cookies used at our website <a href="http://www.aunetic.com/">http://www.aunetic.com/</a>:</p>
    <h2>How we use cookies</h2>
    <p>We use device identifiers to adapt the content and ads for the users, to provide functions for our social media, and to analyze our website traffic. Moreover, we transmit such identifiers and other information from your device to the social media, marketing, and analytics companies which we cooperate with. These companies may combine the information collected at our website with other types of information that they have about you.</p>
    <p>Cookies are small text files used to improve the efficiency of a user’s experience. The law allows us to store cookies on your device if they are necessary for the functionality of the website. For all other purposes, we need your consent to store cookies on your device.</p>
    <p>This website uses different types of cookies. Some of the cookies at our website are placed by third parties shown at Aunetic’s webpage.</p>
    <p>You can change or withdraw your consent to the cookie declaration via this linked page, which you can always access through the cookie in the corner.</p>
    <p>Read more about us, our contact information, and how we process personal data in our privacy policy [link hover over].</p>
    <h2>Information about Albacross’ processing of your personal data</h2>
    <p>We inform you regarding the processing of personal data on behalf of Albacross Nordic AB (“<strong>Albacross</strong>”).</p>
    <p>Information collected from cookies set in your device that qualify as personal data will be processed by Albacross, a platform offering visitor identification and ad targeting services with offices in Stockholm and Krakow. Please see below for full contact details.</p>
    <p>The purpose</strong> for the processing of the personal data is that it enables Albacross to improve a service rendered to us and our website (e.g “Intent” service), by adding data to their database about companies. The Albacross database will in addition to “Intent Data” be used for targeted advertising purposes towards companies and for this purpose data will be transferred to third-party data service providers. For the purpose of clarity, targeted advertising regards companies, not towards individuals. </p>
    <p>The data that is collected and used</strong> by Albacross to achieve this purpose is information about the IP address from which you visited our website and technical information that enables Albacross to tell apart different visitors from the same IP address. Albacross stores the domain from form input in order to correlate the IP address with your employer.</p>
    <p>For full information</strong> about our processing of personal data, please see Albacross’ <a href="https://albacross.com/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
